# https://w3id.org/dqvch#provenance
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#provenance> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#provenance> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dqv#Dimension> .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#provenance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/dqvch#plausibility> .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#provenance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Provenance refers to the degree to which a dataset, including its elements and values, are equipped with verifiable information about its origin."@en .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#provenance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "A death certificate cited as the source for a person's date of death provides verifiable evidence, enhancing the plausibility of the data."@en .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#provenance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Provenance"@en .
