# https://w3id.org/dqvch#syntacticAccuracy
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#syntacticAccuracy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#syntacticAccuracy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dqv#Dimension> .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#syntacticAccuracy> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <https://w3id.org/dqvch#accuracy> .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#syntacticAccuracy> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Syntactic Accuracy refers to the degree to which the dataset conforms to the syntax of the employed data description language and, where applicable, the associated data model."@en .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#syntacticAccuracy> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "In the cultural heritage context, LIDO data should conform to the XML data description language and to the LIDO data model to be syntactically correct."@en .
<https://w3id.org/dqvch#syntacticAccuracy> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Syntactic Accuracy"@en .
